<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
:* [[Image:Assembly_New_Assembly.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_CreateAssembly|Create assembly]]: Add an assembly folder
:* [[Image:Assembly_New_Group.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_GroupObjects|Group objects]]: Group objects
:* [[Image:Assembly_New_Element.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_CreateElement|Create element]]: Create element.
:* Import from STEP. This has two settings
:** [[Image:Assembly_Import.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_ImportFromSTEP|Import from STEP]]: Import STEP files
:** [[Image:Assembly_ImportMulti.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_ImportMultiDocument|Import as multi-document]]: Import assemblies  from STEP into separate documents
:* [[Image:Assembly3_workbench_icon.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_ResolveConstraints|Resolve constraints]]: Resolve constraints
:* [[Image:Assembly_QuickSolve.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_QuickSolve|Quick solve]]: Quick resolve constraints
:* [[Image:Assembly_Move.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_MovePart|Move part]]: Move parts in 3D, this is specific to Assembly3
:* [[Image:Assembly_AxialMove.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_AxialMove|Axial move]]: Axial move parts in 3D, this is the classical tool available elsewhere in FreeCAD
:* [[Image:Assembly_QuickMove.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_QuickMove|Quick move]]: This will attach the part selected in the tree to the mouse cursor. It will change the position of the part when you click. 
:*: Often added parts are stacked upon each other in the origin. Use this function to grab a part you can not see.
:* [[Image:Assembly_LockMover.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_LockMover|Lock mover]]: Lock mover for fixed part. Toggle Button. When this is un-selected you can move the parts that have a "Locked" constraint.
:* [[Image:Assembly_TogglePartVisibility.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_TogglePartVisibility|Toggle part visibility]]: This toggles the visiblity of the selected part on/off.
:*: Note that this differs from using space. Using space with selected items from a sub-assembly in the 3D view often does not behave as expected. Use this function in those cases (or shortcut A-Space)
:* [[Image:Assembly_Trace.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_TracePartMove|Trace part move]]: Trace part move (TBD)
:* [[Image:Assembly_AutoRecompute.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_AutoRecompute|Auto recompute]]: Auto recompute. Usually enabled.
:*: May be un-selected when repairing constraints or fixing parts where the solver gives a ''"do not converge"'' message (e.g. by turning the part 180deg) 
:* [[Image:Assembly_SmartRecompute.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_SmartRecompute|Smart recompute]]: Smart recompute. Usually enabled.
:* [[Image:Assembly_AutoFixElement.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_AutoFixElement|Auto fix element]]: Element Auto Fixing. Experimental feature in 0.19_pre
:* Element Style. This has two settings
:** [[Image:Assembly_AutoElementVis.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_AutoElementVisibility|Auto element visibility]]: Auto element visibility
:** [[Image:Assembly_ShowElementCS.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_ShowElementCS|Show element coordinate system]]: Show element coordinate system
:* Workplane and origin. Adds a workplane, placement or origin. A part must be selected. This has five settings
:** [[Image:Assembly_Add_Workplane.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_AddWorkplane|Add workplane]]: Add workplane
:** [[Image:Assembly_Add_WorkplaneXZ.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_AddXZWorkplane|Add XZ workplane]]: Add XZ workplane
:** [[Image:Assembly_Add_WorkplaneZY.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_AddZYWorkplane|Add ZY workplane]]: Add YZ workplane
:** [[Image:Assembly_Add_Placement.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_AddPlacement|Add placement]]: Add placement
:** [[Image:Assembly_Add_Origin.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_AddOrigin|Add Origin]]: Add Origin
:* [[Image:Assembly_TreeItemUp.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_MoveItemUp|Move item up]]: Move selected tree item up
:* [[Image:Assembly_TreeItemDown.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_MoveItemDown|Move item down]]: Move selected tree item down
:*: Allows to sort Parts, Elements or Constraints in the tree. Element roll over (top to bottom and vice versa). Only works for a single selection. 
:* [[Image:Assembly_ConstraintMultiply.svg‚Äé‚Äé|32px]] [[Assembly3_MultiplyConstraint|Multiply constraint]]: Multiply Constraint. This can be selected if multiple parts and suitable Elements are present. 
:*: It is used e.g. to assign multiple fasteners of the same type into multiple holes with one constraint.
